{
  "texts": [
    "Super-Resolution TechnologyDue to the complexity of traffic scenes, images obtained from traffic scenes, especially those depicting small objects, often have low quality.",
    "External environmental factors and the characteristics of traffic objects themselves contribute to this complexity.",
    "Image quality is crucial for vision-based detectors because low-quality images typically result in poor detection results.",
    "However, high-resolution images can be beneficial for small object detection as they provide finer details about the original scene [57].",
    "Some pioneering works [58][59][60] have been reported in the field of super-resolution (SR) for large-sized inputs, such as videos and 3D scans.Reference [61]proposed training an image-specific Generative Adversarial Network (GAN) called Kernel GAN to model the degradation process, i.e., the blur kernel."
  ]
}